@page "/"

<div class="container mt-5">

    <!-- Home / Landing -->
    <div id="home" class="section d-flex flex-column justify-content-center align-items-center">
        <h1>Hi, I'm Paul Saltzman</h1>
        <p>Welcome to my developer portfolio!</p>
        <a class="btn btn-primary mt-3" href="#projects">View Projects</a>
    </div>

    <!-- About -->
    <section id="about" class="section d-flex flex-column justify-content-center align-items-center">
        <h2 class="text-center mb-4">About</h2>
        <p class="text-start">
            Hi, I’m Paul Saltzman — an aspiring full-stack developer with a unique blend of design, software support, and database experience.
        </p>
        <p class="text-start">
            I began my career with a degree in Graphic Design and several years in web design, which gave me a strong foundation in building clean, user-friendly interfaces. 
            For the past 13 years, I’ve worked in software support, where I’ve gained deep experience understanding business systems, troubleshooting, and working closely with data.
            In my role, I work with Microsoft SQL Server, MariaDB, and DB2, where I’ve learned database structure and written reports to support business needs
            Over the last 3 years, I’ve been expanding my skills into software development, including creating a data conversion program at my current job.
            My goal is to bridge the gap between design, data, and development by moving into full-time full-stack development, bringing together creativity,
            problem-solving, and technical knowledge.
        </p>
        <p class="text-start">
            Outside of coding, I enjoy blacksmithing, 3D printing, tinkering with my home server, and walking my dogs. These hobbies fuel my curiosity and creativity — the same qualities I bring into my professional growth as a developer.
        </p>
    </section>

